<h1>Problem 1516 - 2005 IMO, P2 of 6, AN</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Let \(a_1,a_2,\ldots\) be a sequence of integers with infinitely many positive and negative terms. Suppose that for every positive integer \(n\) the numbers \(a_1,a_2,\ldots,a_n\) leave \(n\) different remainders upon division by \(n\).</p>
<p>Prove that every integer occurs exactly once in the sequence \(a_1,a_2,\ldots\).</p>
